following up by f7-f5.}) (10. Nd2 Be6 {[%csl Gd5]} ({worthy of consideration is
} 10... Rb8 $5) 11. f4 {another example here} (11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. Nd5 {[%csl
Gd5] all this occured in Remizov-Buksa, Lichess. org INT 2021 Black should
have played} Bg5 $146 13. Nf3 Bh6 {[%csl Gh6]} 14. c3 g6 $132 {[%cal Gg8h8,
Gf7f5] following up by Kh8 and keeping in mind f7-f5 advance. Black has
adequate game.}) 11... exf4 12. Bxf4 {Espinosa Veloz-Filgueiras,N Chess.com
INT 2020 here I would like to suggest the following improvement} Qd7 $1 $146
13. Kh1 Rae8 {[%cal Gd6d5] Black fully equalised , additionally} 14. Nd5 $140
$2 {is not possible in view of} Bxd5 15. exd5 Nb4 {[%csl Gd5]}) 10... Rb8 11.
Bxf6 ({Another example would be} 11. Qd2 {Savitha Shri,B-Vantika, A New Delhi
