like to mention here is} O-O 8. f4 {a natural follow up It's been
well-established that Black main move in this position is 8...Bg4, however,
while working on this line I noticed that recently Black has successfully
started to implement} a6 $5 {[%cal Gb7b5] and this continuation will be our
main move. The vast majority of games have been played in correspondence games,
but in my opinion, it only adds value to this line. First of all, it's good
news for Black that seemingly tempting} 9. f5 {is not dangerous Black and
therefore happened only once} (9. Nf3 b5 10. Bb3 Bg4 ({Worthy of consideration
is} 10... Nd4 $5 $146 11. fxe5 {maybe White should opt for} (11. Nxd4 exd4 12.
Nd5 {although it seems that after} Be6 {Black position is quite solid.}) 11...
dxe5 12. Nxe5 Be6 $44 {with very interesting compensation for sacrificed pawn.}
) 11. h3 ({Once again I examined} 11. f5 $146 {It looks quite scary, however
Black is fine after} Nd4 12. Nd5 Kh8 $1 {A good prophylaxis moving the king
away from a2-g8 diagonal and getting ready for opening up the g-file} 13. Nxf6
Bxf3 14. gxf3 Nxb3 {preventing Bd5-move} 15. axb3 Bxf6 16. Kh1 g6 $1 $15 {
and it looks like Black is taking over.}) 11... Bxf3 12. Qxf3 ({Another game
saw} 12. Rxf3 Nd4 {[%csl Gf3]} 13. Rf2 Rc8 {[%cal Gc5c4]} 14. a3 {[%csl Ga2]}
Nxb3 15. cxb3 Re8 $5 {The immediate 15...b4 was absolutely fine as well.} 16.
Qf3 b4 $1 {[%csl Gc3]} 17. Ne2 Nd7 18. axb4 cxb4 {[%cal Gd7c5]} 19. Be3 {
here Black played ambitious} d5 $5 (19... Rc2 {was good enough for equality.})
20. exd5 exf4 21. Qxf4 Nf6 {[%csl Gd5]} 22. Ng3 Rc5 $5 23. Bxc5 Bxc5 24. Rxa6
Qxd5 25. Rxf6 Bxf2+ 26. Qxf2 gxf6 27. Ne4 {[%csl Gf6]} Rxe4 {After wild
complications the position simplified and draw agreed in Oprisor,R-Odrov,V
ICCF email 2015}) 12... Nd4 {[%csl Gf3]} 13. Qd1 a5 {[%cal Ga5a4]} (13... Rc8
$5 {[%cal Gc5c4] deserves attaention as well}) 14. a4 b4 15. Nb5 Nxb3 16. cxb3
Rc8 17. Be3 Qd7 {with a very complex game in Jimena Bonillo, S-Sitorus,Y ICCF
email 2017}) (9. a3 {has been played several times} Bg4 {[%csl Gd1]} 10. Qd2 ({
The alternative is} 10. Nf3 exf4 11. Bxf4 Nd4 12. Kh1 {preparing for opening
up of the g-file} b5 {[%csl Gc4]} 13. Ba2 Kh8 {Always useful move in
